It&#8217;s understood that five men targeted a jewellery store at the Festival Mall at about 2pm on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - Two people have been shot and wounded in a mall robbery in Kempton Park on Monday afternoon.It s understood that five men targeted a jewellery store at the Festival Mall at about 2pm.There was a shootout between the owner of the store and the suspects, in which a female employee was wounded in the leg.The suspects then shot a security guard on their way out.ER24 s Russel Meiring says both victims have been taken to hospital. Paramedics found the security guard lying in the parking lot of the mall. The man was assessed and found to be in a critical condition after he sustained a gunshot wound to his chest. He apparently tried to defend himself before he sustained the wound. 